ggplot(data = corruptDF, mapping = aes(x = HDI2017, y = CPI2017)) + 
  geom_point() +
labs(x = "HDI2017", y = "CPI2017",
       title = "Relationship between HDI2017 and CPI2017") +  
  geom_smooth(method = "gam", se = FALSE)
`geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ s(x, bs = "cs")'

After using both the âlmâ and âgamâ methods of geom_smooth(), I realized that the âgamâ method, in my opinion, better suits the correlation more accurately. The âlmâ method provides a more linear path while the âgamâmethod provides a more exponential path.
